On-Demand Self-Service - Available when you need it. 

Scalability - Ability to scale up and down based on the needs of the organization

Horizontal Scaling - Adding more servers to the server pool to meet demand. 

Vertical Scaling - Increasing the capacity of existing servers. Adding more resources (CPU memory) to existing servers to meet increased demand.

Elasticity - Concept of Expanding and Contracting quickly and refers to increasing and decreasing capacity as short term needs fluctuate. 

Broad Network Access - Anytime, Anywhere access. 

Measured Service - Pay for only what you consume. Everything in the cloud is metered. 